theorem Topology.dense_iff_interior_compl_eq_empty
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Dense A ↔ interior (Aᶜ) = (∅ : Set X) := by
  classical
  constructor
  · intro hDense
    -- A dense set has empty interior complement.
    exact Topology.interior_compl_eq_empty_of_dense (A := A) hDense
  · intro hIntEmpty
    -- We prove that `closure A = univ`, hence `A` is dense.
    have hClosureEq : closure A = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
      -- It suffices to show the complement of `closure A` is empty.
      have hComplEmpty : (closure A)ᶜ = (∅ : Set X) := by
        apply Set.eq_empty_iff_forall_not_mem.2
        intro x hxComp
        -- `((closure A)ᶜ)` is an open subset of `Aᶜ`, hence contained
        -- in `interior (Aᶜ)`, contradicting the hypothesis.
        have hOpen : IsOpen ((closure A)ᶜ) :=
          isClosed_closure.isOpen_compl
        have hSubset : ((closure A)ᶜ : Set X) ⊆ Aᶜ := by
          intro y hy
          by_contra hAy
          -- If `y ∈ A`, then `y ∈ closure A`, contradicting `hy`.
          have : y ∈ closure A := subset_closure hAy
          exact hy this
        have hxInt : x ∈ interior (Aᶜ) :=
          (interior_maximal hSubset hOpen) hxComp
        simpa [hIntEmpty] using hxInt
      -- With an empty complement, the closure is the whole space.
      simpa [hComplEmpty] using Set.compl_compl (closure A)
    -- Translate the equality into the `Dense` predicate.
    exact (Topology.dense_iff_closure_eq_univ (A := A)).2 hClosureEq

theorem Topology.closure_interior_union_frontier
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    closure (interior A) ∪ frontier A = closure A := by
  ext x
  constructor
  · intro hx
    cases hx with
    | inl h_cl_int =>
        -- `closure (interior A)` is contained in `closure A`
        have h_sub : closure (interior A) ⊆ closure A :=
          closure_mono (interior_subset : interior A ⊆ A)
        exact h_sub h_cl_int
    | inr h_front =>
        -- Points in the frontier of `A` lie in `closure A`
        exact h_front.1
  · intro hx_clA
    by_cases h_intA : x ∈ interior A
    · -- If `x ∈ interior A`, then it is in `closure (interior A)`
      have : x ∈ closure (interior A) := subset_closure h_intA
      exact Or.inl this
    · -- Otherwise, `x` belongs to the frontier of `A`
      have : x ∈ frontier A := And.intro hx_clA h_intA
      exact Or.inr this
